The method returns a long integer representing the number of distinct ways to buy pens and pencils.
The returned value is always non-negative.
Additional requirements:
The method should handle large input values efficiently.
The method should handle cases where the cost of pen and pencil are equal to the total money. In this case, the method should return 1.
The method should handle cases where the cost of pen and pencil are both greater than the total money. In this case, the method should return 0.
